ward|Obie]] for playwriting, Kesselring Prize, The Best Plays of 2001\u201302 for ''[sic] ''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.villagevoice.com/obies/search |title=New York Search Obies Theater Awards |publisher=Villagevoice.com |date=2012-10-17 |accessdate=2013-05-22 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130530010535/http://www.villagevoice.com/obies/search/ |archivedate=2013-05-30 }}</ref>\n* 2002 [[Whiting Awards|Whiting Award]] <ref>{{cite web|title=2002 Winner in Drama|url=http://www.whiting.org/awards/winners/melissa-james-gibson#/|website=whiting.or|publisher=Whiting Foundation}}</ref>\n* 2011 [http://broadwayworld.com/article/BWW-TV-2011-Steinberg-Playwrights-Awards-Honors-Melissa-James-Gibson-and-Lisa-DAmour-Inside-the-Event-20111115 Steinberg Playwright Award]\n\n==Works==\n* ''God's Paws'' (1993).\n* ''Six Fugues'' (1995).\n* [https://books.google.com/books?id=NAjEKscAyCIC&printsec=frontcover&dq=Melissa+James+Gibson&cd=1#v=onepage&q=&f=false ''&#91;sic&#93;''], [[Steppenwolf Theatre Company]] commission, New York Premiere: [[Soho Rep]] (2001).\n* ''Suitcase, or Those That Resemble Flies From A Distance'' (NEA/ TCG Theatre Residency Program), [[Soho Rep]] (2004).\n* ''Brooklyn Bridge'', music by Barbara Brousal (The Children's Theater Company/New Dramatists Playground program commission) (2005).\n* ''Current Nobody'', Woolly Mammoth Theatre Company, DC, (2007).\n* ''Nuda Veritas'', Philadelphia Fringe Festival (2009).\n* ''This'', [[Playwrights Horizons]], (2009).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theatermania.com/off-broadway/news/12-2009/melissa-james-gibsons-this-extends-at-playwrights_23380.html |title=Melissa James Gibson's This Extends at Playwrights Horizons Through January 3 \u2013 Theater News \u2013 Dec 7, 2009 |publisher=Theatermania.com |date=2009-12-07 |accessdate=2013-05-22}}</ref> Canadian Premiere: [[Vancouver Playhouse Theatre Company|Vancouver Playhouse]], January 2011, directed by Amiel Gladstone.\n* ''What Rhymes With Ameri